<doc id="1941" url="http://witcher.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1941" title="TheWitcherSave format">
TheWitcherSave format

"The Witcher" uses a format called Rich Saved Game file that always end in TheWitcherSave extension. The format appears to be organized as follows:
Resource table.
Contains list of Resource Table Entries.
Coda.
Read from the bottom of the file:
External links.
WitchSav - tk102's savegame unpacker/repacker

</doc>
<doc id="1942" url="http://witcher.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1942" title="KEY BIF V1.1 format">
KEY BIF V1.1 format

With the &lt;samp&gt;.BIF&lt;/samp&gt; / &lt;samp&gt;.KEY&lt;/samp&gt; file formats you can extract the individual data files from any source in "The Witcher". The KEY v1.1 file format is organized as follows:
Nametable.
Contains packed strings of &lt;samp&gt;BIF&lt;/samp&gt; names.
BIF v1.1 File Format.
The &lt;samp&gt;BIF&lt;/samp&gt; v1.1 file format is organized as follows:
Resource Data.
Contains packed binary resources.

