 &lt;header&gt;Additional Information&lt;/header&gt;
 &lt;data source="type"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Type&lt;/label&gt;&lt;format&gt;Contract quest&lt;/format&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="related"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Related&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="id"&gt;&lt;label&gt;ID&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;/group&gt;
&lt;/infobox&gt;
The Barghest Contract is a contract quest in "The Witcher".
The Barghest Contract
"Brave man urgently needed! Whoever brings me 10 barghest skulls will receive 100 orens."
"Abigail, herbalist"
Walkthrough.
The quest should not be a problem at all. You will find barghests just everywhere in the Outskirts at night. Look for rabid dogs or do the quest She's No Early Bird - both are guaranteed locations for barghests. After you have collected ten skulls, see Abigail for a nice XP boost and some coin.
Phases.
Barghest Skulls.
Abigail, the local herbalist, will pay cash for barghest skulls. I should see her as soon as I collect the number she needs. "I must collect ten barghest skulls for Abigail."
Loot.
I have enough barghest skulls to collect my reward. I should see Abigail. "I should see Abigail and collect my reward."
Payment.
Abigail paid me for the barghest skulls. Job done. "I received my reward for the barghest skulls." (100 + 2000 XP)
Failed.
I doubt anyone will want these barghest skulls now. These barghest skulls are useless now.

</doc>
<doc id="1985" url="http://witcher.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1985" title="The Drowner Contract">
The Drowner Contract

"Something wrong with my face?"&lt;br&gt;This article or its infobox is missing an image. You can help by it.&lt;br&gt;Please do not upload images from other fan sites unless it's official artwork.
&lt;infobox&gt;
 &lt;title source="name"&gt;&lt;format&gt;The Drowner Contract&lt;/format&gt;&lt;default&gt;The Drowner Contract&lt;/default&gt;&lt;/title&gt;
 &lt;image source="image" /&gt;
 &lt;group&gt;
 &lt;header&gt;Description&lt;/header&gt;
 &lt;data source="module"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Module&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="chapter"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Chapter(s)&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="location"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Location(s)&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="given by"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Given by&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="reward"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Reward&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;/group&gt;
 &lt;group&gt;
 &lt;header&gt;Additional Information&lt;/header&gt;
 &lt;data source="type"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Type&lt;/label&gt;&lt;format&gt;Contract quest&lt;/format&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="related"&gt;&lt;label&gt;Related&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;data source="id"&gt;&lt;label&gt;ID&lt;/label&gt;&lt;/data&gt;
 &lt;/group&gt;
&lt;/infobox&gt;
The Drowner Contract
"The Church of the Eternal Fire seeks individuals capable of dealing with the drowners at the riverbank. Payment is contingent on supplying proof of killing three of the beasts. Bring their brains. Inquire with the Reverend."
Walkthrough.
Drowners are always easy prey. They are very susceptible to stun attempts, so use your Aard sign often. If you wear a red ribbon Talisman (which can be bought from Abigail) they will not attack at all, but you will have to chase them around to kill them. Talk to the Reverend to collect your reward after you have collected three drowner brains.
Phases.
Drowner Brains.
The Church of the Eternal Fire has offered a reward for killing drowners. The brains of the monsters must be presented as proof of their demise. "I need to collect three drowner brains for the Reverend."
Loot.
I've collected enough drowner brains. Time to find a priest of the Eternal Fire. "I should see the Reverend and collect my reward."
Payment.
I delivered the drowner brains. Job done. "I received my reward for the drowner brains." (100 + 2000 XP)
Failed.
I doubt I'll have another chance to complete this assignment. I lost my chance to collect that reward.

</doc>
<doc id="1986" url="http://witcher.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1986" title="The Ghoul Contract (1)">
The Ghoul Contract (1)

&lt;infobox&gt;
 &lt;title source="name"&gt;&lt;format&gt;The Ghoul Contract&lt;/format&gt;&lt;default&gt;The Ghoul Contract (1)&lt;/default&gt;&lt;/title&gt;
 &lt;image source="image" /&gt;
